The paper deals with a variation of the stable marriage problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and operations research. The use of local search algorithms to solve combinatorial optimization problems is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS) research. The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of the problem, which is related to game theory (cs.GT). The authors also mention experimental results, which suggests that the paper may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
